Smartphone Class - Python OOP Assignment
📖 Overview

This project demonstrates Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts in Python by creating a simple Smartphone class.
The class includes attributes, methods, and shows the use of constructors and inheritance.

🏗️ Features

Device (Parent Class):

Stores basic details like brand and model.

Has a method device_info() to display device details.

Smartphone (Child Class):

Inherits from Device.

Adds extra attributes: storage (in GB) and battery (in mAh).

Methods:

phone_info() → shows full phone details.

charge(amount) → simulates charging the phone.

install_app(app_name, size) → installs an app and reduces available storage.

📝 Example Usage
phone1 = Smartphone("Samsung", "Galaxy S21", 128, 4000)
phone2 = Smartphone("Apple", "iPhone 13", 256, 3500)

print(phone1.phone_info())  
# Output: Device: Samsung Galaxy S21, Storage: 128GB, Battery: 4000mAh

print(phone1.install_app("WhatsApp", 2))  
# Output: Installed WhatsApp. Remaining storage: 126GB

print(phone1.charge(500))  
# Output: Galaxy S21 charged! New battery level: 4500mAh

🎯 Concepts Shown

Class & Object creation

Constructors (__init__)

Inheritance

Encapsulation of attributes & methods

Polymorphism (overriding device_info in child class)